modules.description: Parses dBase database files by reading header information and records, extracting field names, types, and values. Works with byte streams and structured data representing database fields and rows. Used to load and process dBase data for analysis or migration tasks.

Provides functions to parse and manipulate dBase database files, including reading field definitions, date values, and record data. Operates on structured types such as headers, fields, dates, and records with specific formatting rules. Used to extract and process data from .dbf files in applications requiring direct access to legacy database formats.
